The key point is that OLAPSet could join each other.
For instance,
var customerSet:OLAPSet = new OLAPSet;
customerSet.addElements(cube.findDimension(&ldquo;CustomerDim&rdquo;).findAttribute(&ldquo;Customer&rdquo;).children);
var quarterSet:OLAPSet = new OLAPSet;
quarterSet.addElements(cube.findDimension(&ldquo;QuarterDim&rdquo;).findAttribute(&ldquo;Quarter&rdquo;).children);
colQueryAxis.addSet(quarterSet.crossJoin(customerSet));

Testing scenario: If testArray contains target at position n, then binarySearch (testArray, target) must return _n
